  <h2><a href="../../blog-posts/complexities-us-decision-chinese-solar-panel-imports" title="The Complexities of the U.S. Decision on Chinese Solar Panel Imports">The Complexities of the U.S. Decision on Chinese Solar Panel Imports</a></h2>

      <span class="submitted">Posted by ChinaFAQs on Mar 19, 2012</span>
  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <div class="field field-type-filefield field-field-image">
    <div class="field-items">
            <div class="field-item odd">
                    <img src="../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/OregonDOT_SolarPanels.jpg" alt="" title="" width="179" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/>        </div>
        </div>
</div>
<p>This week, the U.S. Department of Commerce is expected to issue a preliminary decision on a trade petition filed by SolarWorld Industries America, Inc. SolarWorld alleges that the Chinese have used subsidies to artificially suppress solar panel export prices, and has asked Commerce to levy a duty to eliminate that price discrepancy. 
<br />
<br />ChinaFAQs expert <A href="../../expert/melanie-hart">Melanie Hart</a> and Kate Gordon at the Center for American Progress analyze this trade case and the implications of the decision for the U.S. solar industry and U.S. energy policy in <A href="http://www.americanprogress.org/issues/2012/03/china_solar_panels.html">&#8220;The Complexities of the U.S. Decision on Chinese Solar Panel Imports.&#8221;</a></p>
  </div>
<div class="clear-block">
    	<div class="readmore"> <a href="../../blog-posts/complexities-us-decision-chinese-solar-panel-imports">Read more</a> </div>
  </div>

  <div class="clear-block">
    <div class="meta">
        </div>

          <div class="links"><ul class="links inline"><li class="node_read_more first last"><a href="../../blog-posts/complexities-us-decision-chinese-solar-panel-imports" title="Read the rest of The Complexities of the U.S. Decision on Chinese Solar Panel Imports.">Read more</a></li>
</ul></div>
      </div>

