  <h2><a href="../../blog-posts/china-promotes-south-south-cooperation-durban" title="China promotes South-South Cooperation in Durban">China promotes South-South Cooperation in Durban</a></h2>

      <span class="submitted">Posted by Angel Hsu on Jan 10, 2012</span>
  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <div class="field field-type-filefield field-field-image">
    <div class="field-items">
            <div class="field-item odd">
                    <img src="../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/IMG_8150.JPG" alt="" title="" width="90" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/>        </div>
        </div>
</div>
<body>
<p>As part of its green diplomacy strategy and move to promote a positive image in Durban, China for the first time highlighted its own development aid in the context of South-South capacity building and financial assistance with least-developed countries (LDCs) and small-island states (SIDs).</p>

<p>On December 5, Xie Zhenhua, NDRC Vice Minister and head of the Chinese delegation in Durban, announced four major areas of investment through South-South collaboration, including...</p>
</body>  </div>
