  <h2><a href="../../blog-posts/global-growth-‚%2580%2593-story-china-wind-power-2011" title="Global Growth ‚Äì  the Story at China Wind Power 2011">Global Growth ‚Äì  the Story at China Wind Power 2011</a></h2>

      <span class="submitted">Posted by Deborah Seligsohn on Oct 24, 2011</span>
  
  <div class="content clear-block">
    <div class="field field-type-filefield field-field-image">
    <div class="field-items">
            <div class="field-item odd">
                    <img src="../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/windturbs.jpg" alt="" title="" width="168" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/>        </div>
        </div>
</div>
<p>China once again hosted its largest wind power expo, <A href="http://www.chinawind.org.cn/home.html">China Wind 2011</a>, surpassing <A href="../../blog-posts/two-international-conferences-china-highlight-importance-wind-energy">last year‚Äôs exhibition</a> with the number of companies and the exhibition floor space increasing by 50%.  Not surprisingly for an event in Beijing, the China market continued to be a major focus, but this year there was much more sense of a global market with increasing interest in new emerging markets, in particular Latin America.</p>
  </div>
<div class="clear-block">
    	<div class="readmore"> <a href="../../blog-posts/global-growth-‚%2580%2593-story-china-wind-power-2011">Read more</a> </div>
